---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
	title="ContextCake Packs - portable context for real team workflows"
	description="Profession-specific ContextCake packs give small teams reusable AI context they can inspect, edit, and carry across tools."
>
	<main class="packs-index">
		<section class="intro">
			<p class="eyebrow">ContextCake Packs</p>
			<h1>Portable context kits for teams that repeat the same work in every AI tool.</h1>
			<p>
				Packs are plain-file bundles with workflows, templates, examples, and tool guidance.
				They sit under the ContextCake brand, but the first pack is sold and fulfilled
				separately from the open-source engine.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="featured" aria-labelledby="featured-pack">
			<div class="pack-marker" aria-hidden="true">
				<span></span>
				<span></span>
				<span></span>
			</div>
			<div>
				<p class="status">First pack</p>
				<h2 id="featured-pack">Data & Analytics Teams</h2>
				<p>
					For the recurring path from stakeholder request to clarified spec, validated build,
					and insight summary.
				</p>
			</div>
			<a href="/packs/data-analytics-teams">View pack</a>
		</section>

		<section class="bench" aria-labelledby="bench-title">
			<h2 id="bench-title">On the bench</h2>
			<p>
				Grant teams, GovCon/RFP, HR, and Insurance remain candidate packs. They wait until
				there is real design-partner access instead of only a paper score.
			</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Base>

<style>
	.packs-index {
		max-width: 72rem;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 4rem 1.5rem 2rem;
	}
	.intro {
		max-width: 54rem;
	}
	.eyebrow,
	.status {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		color: var(--cc-layer-team);
		font-family: var(--cc-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}
	h1 {
		max-width: 12ch;
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(3.1rem, 8vw, 6.8rem);
		line-height: 0.94;
		letter-spacing: 0;
	}
	.intro p:last-child,
	.bench p,
	.featured p {
		max-width: 62ch;
		color: var(--cc-text-body);
		font-size: 1.12rem;
	}
	.featured {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: auto minmax(0, 1fr) auto;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 4rem;
		padding: 1.5rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--cc-border);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--cc-border);
	}
	.pack-marker {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.35rem;
		width: 4rem;
	}
	.pack-marker span {
		display: block;
		height: 0.85rem;
		border-radius: 3px;
	}
	.pack-marker span:nth-child(1) {
		background: var(--cc-layer-personal);
		margin-left: 0.8rem;
	}
	.pack-marker span:nth-child(2) {
		background: var(--cc-layer-team);
	}
	.pack-marker span:nth-child(3) {
		background: var(--cc-layer-company);
		margin-left: 0.4rem;
	}
	.featured h2,
	.bench h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);
		line-height: 1;
		letter-spacing: 0;
	}
	.featured a {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		min-height: 44px;
		padding: 0 1rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--cc-cta);
		border-radius: 6px;
		color: var(--cc-canvas);
		background: var(--cc-cta);
		font-weight: 700;
		text-decoration: none;
		white-space: nowrap;
	}
	.bench {
		margin-top: 4rem;
		max-width: 44rem;
	}
	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.featured {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
		.featured a {
			justify-content: center;
			width: fit-content;
		}
	}
</style>
